```

This should match: when both LHS and RHS are selects with the same condition (A == D), and B == F and C == E (i.e., the true of one is the false of the other and vice versa), then for commutative ops it simplifies to B op C.

But the issue is that this code is inside the `if (LHSIsSelect && RHSIsSelect && A == D)` block (line 1134). The condition A == D checks if the select conditions are the same. So this should work.

But wait - the issue says the optimization is not happening. Let me think about why...

The source program:
```llvm
  %.sink = select i1 %c, i8 %a, i8 %b
  %add.sink = select i1 %c, i8 %b, i8 %a
